---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// ── EDIT THESE two placeholders once your accounts are live ───────────────
const CALENDAR_URL = 'https://cal.com/velidion/intro'; // TODO: your booking link
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'hello@velidion.com';            // TODO: your inbox
// Email capture posts here. Sign up for a free form endpoint (Formspree,
// Buttondown, ConvertKit, Tally) and paste the action URL below.
const EMAIL_FORM_ACTION = ''; // TODO: e.g. https://formspree.io/f/xxxxxxx
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
---

<Layout>
  <!-- ============================ NAV ============================ -->
  <header class="nav">
    <div class="wrap nav__row">
      <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="Velidion home">
        <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true">
          <rect width="32" height="32" rx="7" fill="#1a2b3c"></rect>
          <path d="M8 9.5 L15 22 L24 7" fill="none" stroke="#4a9fc4"
                stroke-width="3.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
        Velidion
      </a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#talk">Talk to us</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- ============================ HERO ============================ -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="eyebrow">Compliance infrastructure for safety-critical engineering</span>
        <h1>Proving your engineering is safe shouldn&rsquo;t be the hardest part of building it.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Velidion is building the operating system for engineering compliance in
          safety-critical industries &mdash; the traceability, the evidence, the sign-offs,
          the audit trail &mdash; starting with the small regulated teams the incumbents
          have priced out.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__cta">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#talk">Talk to us &rarr;</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#updates">Get updates</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__status">
          <span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          Early days &mdash; we&rsquo;re in research, talking to engineering, quality, and
          regulatory teams about how compliance really works.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========================== PROBLEM ========================== -->
    <section>
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">The problem</span>
          <h2>Regulation isn&rsquo;t the hard part. Proving it is.</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            In medical devices, aerospace, automotive, and energy, the law doesn&rsquo;t
            just require you to build safely &mdash; it requires you to <em>prove</em> it.
            Every requirement traced to a test. Every change reviewed and signed. Every
            hazard documented and reconstructable years later. Today that proof lives in
            fragile spreadsheets and shared drives &mdash; or in enterprise tools that cost
            tens of thousands a year and lock you in for three.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat__num">70&ndash;80%</div>
            <div class="stat__txt">
              of FDA 510(k) submissions miss the 90-day review target &mdash; mostly on
              process and paperwork, not the underlying science.
            </div>
            <div class="stat__src">
              <a href="https://qualysec.com/fda-510k-timeline/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Qualysec, 2025</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat__num">$25&ndash;60k/yr</div>
            <div class="stat__txt">
              plus multi-year lock-in &mdash; what small teams pay incumbent compliance
              tools, when they can afford them at all. Many churn back to spreadsheets.
            </div>
            <div class="stat__src">
              <a href="https://openregulatory.com/articles/greenlight-guru-price" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRegulatory, 2025</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat__num">147&times;</div>
            <div class="stat__txt">
              the rise in the annual rate of FDA AI/ML medical-device authorizations over
              three decades. The amount that has to be proven is only growing.
            </div>
            <div class="stat__src">
              <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41746-025-01800-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">npj Digital Medicine, 2025</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========================== BELIEF =========================== -->
    <section class="tint">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">What we believe</span>
          <h2>When software gets cheap, the workflow is the moat.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="beliefs">
          <div class="belief">
            <div class="belief__k">01</div>
            <h3>AI is doing two things at once</h3>
            <p>
              It&rsquo;s multiplying the things that must be proven safe &mdash; AI-enabled
              devices, autonomous robots, a new generation of energy infrastructure &mdash;
              and it&rsquo;s making ordinary software cheap to build.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="belief">
            <div class="belief__k">02</div>
            <h3>Features stop being a moat</h3>
            <p>
              When anyone can ship a feature overnight, the durable thing isn&rsquo;t the
              feature. It&rsquo;s the workflow itself: the evidence, the traceability, the
              accumulated trust that can&rsquo;t be cloned on a funding round.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="belief">
            <div class="belief__k">03</div>
            <h3>So we own the proof</h3>
            <p>
              We&rsquo;re not building another tool to bolt on. We&rsquo;re building the
              layer that owns the compliance workflow &mdash; earned one regulated team at a
              time, starting where the pain is sharpest and the tools are worst.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========================= AUDIENCE ========================== -->
    <section class="audience">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="eyebrow">Who we&rsquo;re building with</span>
        <h2>If your compliance lives in a spreadsheet you&rsquo;re afraid to break, we want to talk.</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:20px;">
          We&rsquo;re looking for small engineering, quality, and regulatory teams in
          regulated industries &mdash; medical devices first, but not only. Not to sell you
          anything: we&rsquo;re in the research phase, and the teams we talk to now are the
          ones who shape what we build.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================ CTA ============================ -->
    <section id="talk" class="tint">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">Two ways to be part of this</span>
          <h2>Help shape it &mdash; or just follow along.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-grid">
          <!-- Book a conversation -->
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Talk to us</h3>
            <p>
              30 minutes, no pitch. Walk us through how your team really manages
              requirements, documents, and audits today &mdash; the messy version. It
              genuinely shapes the product.
            </p>
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href={CALENDAR_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Book a conversation &rarr;
            </a>
            <p class="form-note">
              Prefer email? <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}?subject=Compliance%20discovery%20chat`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Email updates -->
          <div id="updates" class="card">
            <h3>Get updates</h3>
            <p>
              Occasional notes on what we&rsquo;re learning about compliance in
              safety-critical industries. No spam, no hype &mdash; unsubscribe anytime.
            </p>
            <form
              class="field"
              action={EMAIL_FORM_ACTION || undefined}
              method="POST"
            >
              <input
                type="email"
                name="email"
                required
                placeholder="you@company.com"
                aria-label="Email address"
                autocomplete="email"
              />
              <button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit">Keep me posted</button>
            </form>
            <p class="form-note">
              {EMAIL_FORM_ACTION
                ? 'We’ll only use this to send occasional updates.'
                : 'Setup: paste your form endpoint into EMAIL_FORM_ACTION in src/pages/index.astro.'}
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- ========================== FOOTER =========================== -->
  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="wrap footer__row">
      <span class="brand" style="font-size:1rem;">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true">
          <rect width="32" height="32" rx="7" fill="#1a2b3c"></rect>
          <path d="M8 9.5 L15 22 L24 7" fill="none" stroke="#4a9fc4"
                stroke-width="3.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
        Velidion
      </span>
      <span>Compliance infrastructure for safety-critical industries.</span>
      <span>&copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} Velidion &middot; <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a></span>
    </div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="notes">
        Figures cited above:
        <a href="https://qualysec.com/fda-510k-timeline/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FDA 510(k) review timelines (Qualysec)</a>;
        <a href="https://openregulatory.com/articles/greenlight-guru-price" target="_blank" rel="noopener">incumbent eQMS pricing (OpenRegulatory)</a>;
        <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41746-025-01800-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FDA AI/ML device authorization growth (npj Digital Medicine)</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
